gate: OPEN
task: S75-TC1
title: Apply Map Type Setting to MapScreen
description: |
  The settings screen has a "Map type" selector (settings?.map field from API,
  options: Open Street / Google Normal / Google Hybrid / Google Satellite).
  MapScreen has its own independent localStorage keys (map_layer, map_provider)
  set by its own UI buttons.
  These two systems are disconnected. The user's settings choice must be reflected
  in MapScreen.

  Current MapScreen layer/provider values:
    - provider: 'osm' | 'google'  → localStorage 'map_provider'
    - layer: LayerType ('osm' | 'satellite' | 'hybrid' | ...)  → localStorage 'map_layer'

  Mapping from Settings.map to MapScreen (map_layer / map_provider):
    'Open Street'      → provider: 'osm',    layer: 'osm'
    'GoogleNormal'     → provider: 'google',  layer: 'normal'
    'GoogleHybrid'     → provider: 'google',  layer: 'hybrid'
    'GoogleSatellite'  → provider: 'google',  layer: 'satellite'

  Steps:
    1. After settings are fetched (useSettingsStore.settings available),
       if settings.map is set and differs from current map_provider/map_layer,
       write the correct values to localStorage AND update MapScreen state.

    2. The cleanest approach: in MapScreen useEffect, subscribe to
       useSettingsStore state changes. When settings.map changes, derive
       provider+layer and apply them (call setProvider + setLayer + persist).

    3. Alternative (simpler): on MapScreen mount, read settings.map from
       useSettingsStore.getState() and initialize provider/layer from it
       (falling back to map_provider/map_layer localStorage if settings.map is null).

    4. When user changes map type in settings-screen TA3, the change must
       propagate to MapScreen on next visit (localStorage is sufficient for this).

    5. Remove the MapScreen layer-switcher UI buttons IF the design decision is
       that map type is managed only from Settings. OR keep them in sync (write
       to localStorage AND call updateSetting({ map: ... })).
       Decision: keep MapScreen buttons, but also update Settings when used
       (call useSettingsStore.updateSetting({ map: derivedValue }) from MapScreen
       handleLayerChange and handleProviderChange callbacks).

acceptance:
  - Selecting "Open Street" in settings → MapScreen shows OSM tiles
  - Selecting "Google Hybrid" in settings → MapScreen shows Google Hybrid tiles
  - MapScreen layer buttons also update the settings value (bidirectional sync)
  - After page reload, map type matches what was last selected (persisted)

requires: [FRONTEND_DEV]
estimated: 2 hours
dep: S75-TA3
